"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-shacarri-richardson-fastest-100m-times-leading-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The athletics (or, as we call it stateside: track & field) portion of the 2024 Paris Games is in full swing, and Sha'Carri Richardson made her Olympics debut on theeye-catching purple trackFriday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 113, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson kicked off her Paris experience with a 10.94-second, opening-heat win to qualify for Saturday's 100-meter semifinal.\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999974093043, \"rank\": 2.590680626631141e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other notables who made it through to the next round in the 100 meters include Jamaica's two-time champion Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce, Marie-Josee Ta Lou-Smith from Ivory Coast with the day's fastest heat of 10.87 seconds, and Richardson's U.S. teammates Melissa Jefferson and Twanisha Terry.\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4851328071541184e-15, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 434, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\"}, {\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999944329829, \"rank\": 4.537815645026495e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melissa Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\"}, {\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Twanisha Terry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson missed the Tokyo Games last time around because of a positive drug test (THC, found in cannabis, banned by the World Doping Federation), and is heralded as one of the fastest sprint runners on the U.S. Track & Field team.\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999944329829, \"rank\": 4.537815645026495e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tetrahydrocannabinol\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8078383728987387e-12, \"text\": \"THC\", \"types\": [\"Q8386\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tetrahydrocannabinol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tetrahydrocannabinol\"}, {\"begin\": 831, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0972630868995612e-71, \"text\": \"Track & Field\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her absence was missed in the Tokyo Games in her main event, but it also underscored a weaker showing from the team all around.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. brought home 26 athletics medals in Tokyo, down from the 32 they secured in Rio 2016 and the 28 they picked up in London 2012.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1025, \"end\": 1030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9592884801384853, \"rank\": 0.04243919460594317, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3888653774685774e-14, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her speed was the expectation and the reality at the U.S. Olympic Team Trials in June, when Richardson was the fastest female in the 100-meter race, securing her spot to run in Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999944329829, \"rank\": 4.537815645026495e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.188063521571654e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are her fastest 10 times recorded in the 100-meter race:  Rank  Time (seconds)  Event  Date  1  10.65  World Athletics Championships  August 21, 2023  2  10.71  USA Championships  July 6, 2024  3  10.71  US Olympic Trials  June 22, 2024  4  10.72  Miramar Invitational  April 10, 2021  5  10.74  USATF Golden Games  May 9, 2021  6  10.75  NCAA Division I Outdoor Championships  June 8, 2019  7  10.75  USA Championships  July 7, 2023  8  10.76  Diamond League Meeting  May 5, 2023  9  10.76  Silesia Kamila Skolimowska Memorial  July 16, 2023  10  10.77  USATF Golden Games  May 9, 2021  At the risk of stating the obvious, Richardson is fast.\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.8606037723102947, \"rank\": 0.1374043878625231, \"text\": \"World Athletics Championships\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_World_Championships_in_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USATF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\"}, {\"begin\": 1936, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999944329829, \"rank\": 4.537815645026495e-09, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans can expect she will compete for a medal on Saturday, and thefirst chance to see her will be on Friday in preliminary and first-round action.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The big race takes place on Saturday, expected around 2:20 p.m.\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She will likely need to log a new personal record in order to medal, presuming her qualification for the final.\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, gold (Elaine Thompson-Herah, Jamacia) was faster than Richardson's PR, with silver and bronze last time around also rivaling some of Richardson's fastest times.\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2286, \"end\": 2291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9592884801384853, \"rank\": 0.04243919460594317, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson-Herah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou